The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 25: Sebi has banned five persons today in the Pyramid Saimira case, who virtually cornered the entire stake meant for employees. The five persons  Kishore S. Jain, Jayantilal R. Jain, Sripal J. Shah, Rajesh Prakash Jain and Praveen Kumar Devi Chand Jain  have been banned from dealing in equities for three years and ordered to return the money with an interest of 20 per cent.                             
	 New Delhi, June 25: Videocon chairman Venugopal Dhoot may join the battle for Great Offshore. I would not sell my 3 per cent stake in Great Offshore. Whether I should go for bidding or keep it will be decided tomorrow. I am meeting my merchant banker for advise on this, Dhoot said.                            
	 New Delhi, June 25: India has imposed an anti-dumping duty of $218.6 per tonne on imports of phosphoric acid, a key ingredient in detergent manufacturing, from South Korea. It has also imposed a duty of up to $1.36 per kg on imports of Diethyl Thio Phosphoryl Chloride, used in pesticides, from China.                             
	 Mumbai, June 25: The RBI today extended the transition period assigned to banks for treating the advances to equity-oriented mutual funds as capital market exposure by six more months.                             
	 Mumbai, June 25: The RBI will come out with the first quarter review of the Monetary Policy on July 28. Chief executives of major scheduled commercial banks will meet on that day.                                                                                                                           
